1
00:01:49,625 --> 00:01:50,875
[TEMUJIN]
Suigin.

2
00:01:50,958 --> 00:01:53,125
I suggest you give me
your full attention.

3
00:01:53,208 --> 00:01:55,500
[SUIGIN] So you’re
the one who kidnapped Rei Riku.

4
00:01:55,583 --> 00:01:57,000
Who the hell is this?

5
00:01:57,083 --> 00:01:59,416
If you’ve hurt her,
I’m talking to a dead man!

6
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:01,875
Oh, spare me
the heroics, would you?

7
00:02:01,958 --> 00:02:03,333
If something were to
happen to her,

8
00:02:03,416 --> 00:02:04,833
how would you stop it?

9
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:05,916
That’s the very reason

10
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,541
we’re keeping
an eye on her.

11
00:02:07,625 --> 00:02:09,875
Ms. Riku
required our protection.

12
00:02:09,958 --> 00:02:11,791
Though she keeps
insisting on calling herself

13
00:02:11,875 --> 00:02:13,208
a hostage,
for some reason.

14
00:02:13,291 --> 00:02:14,291
Where is she?

15
00:02:14,375 --> 00:02:15,583
[TEMUJIN chuckles]

16
00:02:15,666 --> 00:02:18,083
You really want to save her,
don’t you?

17
00:02:18,166 --> 00:02:19,750
Then listen closely.

18
00:02:19,833 --> 00:02:21,250
There’s a festival
being held on

19
00:02:21,333 --> 00:02:23,333
Stage 18
of Grave Buster.

20
00:02:23,416 --> 00:02:24,666
You should attend.

21
00:02:25,666 --> 00:02:27,000
It’s a celebration
for players

22
00:02:27,083 --> 00:02:29,208
who’ve completed
every level in the game.

23
00:02:29,291 --> 00:02:30,500
And a provision
for conquering

24
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:33,000
Stage 0 when
the time comes.

25
00:02:33,083 --> 00:02:34,625
[TEMUJIN]
If you want to beat that level,

26
00:02:34,708 --> 00:02:36,375
which I know you do,

27
00:02:36,458 --> 00:02:38,125
you’ll need to go
to the festival.

28
00:02:38,208 --> 00:02:39,666
Once there,
you’ll have to locate a player

29
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:40,916
named Nishikaze.

30
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,125
Nishikaze?

31
00:02:42,208 --> 00:02:43,583
And how am I
supposed to find a player

32
00:02:43,666 --> 00:02:44,958
I’ve never met before?

33
00:02:45,041 --> 00:02:46,916
Oh, you’ll know
when the time comes.

34
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,250
Give me
a straight answer!

35
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:50,458
What’s this
got to do with

36
00:02:50,541 --> 00:02:51,833
getting Rei back?

37
00:02:51,916 --> 00:02:52,750
[SUIGIN]
Say something!

38
00:02:52,833 --> 00:02:53,708
[phone hangs up]

39
00:02:56,458 --> 00:02:57,666
Damn.

40
00:02:57,750 --> 00:03:00,291
I have no idea
what I’m supposed to do.

41
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:03,000
[sighs softly]

42
00:03:04,541 --> 00:03:06,166
[ANNOUNCER]
He’s the mysterious lone-wolf

43
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:07,666
who never
says a word!

44
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:08,750
The no-charge-meister

45
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:10,291
that showed up
outta nowhere,

46
00:03:10,375 --> 00:03:12,875
defeating enemies with
the lowest grade equipment.

47
00:03:12,958 --> 00:03:14,291
Gwin!

48
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:16,625
♪

49
00:03:17,958 --> 00:03:19,375
[CROWD cheering]

50
00:03:19,458 --> 00:03:23,000
[CROWD chanting]
Gwin! Gwin! Gwin!

51
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:24,625
[REI]
So cool!

52
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:29,083
♪

53
00:03:30,083 --> 00:03:32,750
[SUIGIN] Maybe I was cool
playing in Dungeon Century.

54
00:03:32,833 --> 00:03:34,958
I’m utterly
useless, now.

55
00:03:35,041 --> 00:03:36,083
[WANCHOI meows]

56
00:03:36,166 --> 00:03:36,958
[grunts]

57
00:03:37,041 --> 00:03:39,208
[laughs]
Hey, Wanchoi!

58
00:03:39,291 --> 00:03:41,875
Feels like forever
since I last saw you.

59
00:03:41,958 --> 00:03:43,333
[meows]

60
00:03:45,625 --> 00:03:46,750
[sighs]

61
00:03:49,208 --> 00:03:50,208
[birds chirping]

62
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:52,416
[WANCHOI meowing]

63
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,708
[yawns]

64
00:03:53,791 --> 00:03:55,333
♪

65
00:03:58,458 --> 00:04:00,083
What’re you
meowing at so early?

66
00:04:00,166 --> 00:04:01,083
[meows]

67
00:04:02,125 --> 00:04:04,791
Ah. Looks like some
kind of gathering.

68
00:04:04,875 --> 00:04:06,791
Guess there must be
a celebrity on campus today.

69
00:04:06,875 --> 00:04:08,000
[STUDENTS murmuring]

70
00:04:08,083 --> 00:04:09,500
Has anyone told you
how cute you are?

71
00:04:09,583 --> 00:04:11,916
You should totally join
our cosplay club!

72
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,291
So what school
do you go to?

73
00:04:13,375 --> 00:04:14,833
I’ve never seen you
around before.

74
00:04:14,916 --> 00:04:15,916
Please, date me!

75
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,666
Man, that poor girl.

76
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:19,416
Swarmed over
by a bunch of creeps

77
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,333
who won’t
leave her alone.

78
00:04:21,416 --> 00:04:23,125
[STUDENT 1] What social
media platforms are you on?

79
00:04:23,208 --> 00:04:24,500
Can I get
your e-mail address?

80
00:04:24,583 --> 00:04:25,708
I’ll take anything!

81
00:04:25,791 --> 00:04:27,125
I don’t have one,
all right?

82
00:04:27,208 --> 00:04:28,833
[STUDENT 2] What?
You gotta be kidding!

83
00:04:28,916 --> 00:04:29,958
You’re not online?

84
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:31,375
Do you even
have a social life?

85
00:04:31,458 --> 00:04:32,666
[gasps]

86
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:34,666
[FARIN] What are you
waiting for, Suigin?

87
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:36,041
Are you just
gonna stare all day

88
00:04:36,125 --> 00:04:37,500
or come down here
and save me?

89
00:04:37,583 --> 00:04:38,708
[ALL]
Huh?

90
00:04:38,791 --> 00:04:39,958
[STUDENT 1]
Who’s she talking to?

91
00:04:40,041 --> 00:04:41,041
[STUDENT 2]
It’s that nerd, Suigin!

92
00:04:41,125 --> 00:04:41,708
[STUDENT 3]
Protect her honor!

93
00:04:41,791 --> 00:04:43,083
[gasps]

94
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:44,958
[STUDENT 1]
Don’t get any ideas, pervert!

95
00:04:45,041 --> 00:04:45,916
[STUDENT 3]
Talk about annoying!

96
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,041
[STUDENT 2]
Total loser!

97
00:04:47,125 --> 00:04:48,666
I should've
stayed in bed today!

98
00:04:48,750 --> 00:04:50,333
-What’s the heck’s going on?
-[STUDENT 1] Bastard!

99
00:04:50,416 --> 00:04:52,666
Who’s that girl and
how’s she know me?

100
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:53,916
[meows]

101
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,541
There’s no way.

102
00:04:55,625 --> 00:04:56,666
But,

103
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:58,166
what if it is her?

104
00:04:58,250 --> 00:04:59,375
Farin.

105
00:04:59,458 --> 00:05:00,375
[CROWD chatting]

106
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:06,541
[SUIGIN]
Okay, it is her.

107
00:05:06,625 --> 00:05:07,500
But that
doesn’t explain

108
00:05:07,583 --> 00:05:08,916
why she’s
at my school.

109
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,666
I’m not prepared
to deal with this.

110
00:05:10,750 --> 00:05:12,541
Plus, why’d she
bring a suitcase?

111
00:05:12,625 --> 00:05:13,791
Makes me wonder.

112
00:05:13,875 --> 00:05:16,166
Is she planning on
staying at the dorm?

113
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:17,583
Why am I being so awkward?

114
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:18,833
Come on, Suigin.

115
00:05:18,916 --> 00:05:20,500
Talk to her.

116
00:05:20,583 --> 00:05:21,750
[FARIN]
What are you thinking about?

117
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:22,958
What?
Oh, nothing.

118
00:05:23,041 --> 00:05:24,416
Just, uh, wondering
how you found me,

119
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:25,666
I guess.

120
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,416
I work part-time
as an instructor

121
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:29,250
for the beginner’s
course, remember?

122
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:30,500
So, I was able to
get some

123
00:05:30,583 --> 00:05:32,125
information on you.

124
00:05:32,208 --> 00:05:34,041
Obviously, you aren’t
happy to see me.

125
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,916
So I’ll stop wasting
your time and go.

126
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,500
Huh?
No, I’m glad you’re here

127
00:05:37,583 --> 00:05:39,333
and I get to
see you in person!

128
00:05:39,416 --> 00:05:40,500
[SUIGIN]
Aw, man.

129
00:05:40,583 --> 00:05:41,625
The worst part
is every word

130
00:05:41,708 --> 00:05:43,333
I just said was true.

131
00:05:43,416 --> 00:05:45,458
But now she’s here
and I have zero idea

132
00:05:45,541 --> 00:05:46,583
what to say to her.

133
00:05:46,666 --> 00:05:48,125
[bell dings]

134
00:05:48,208 --> 00:05:49,458
[SUIGIN]
Come to think of it,

135
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:50,625
compared to reality,

136
00:05:50,708 --> 00:05:52,958
I’m a different
person in game.

137
00:05:55,291 --> 00:05:56,875
♪

138
00:05:59,583 --> 00:06:00,625
[SUIGIN]
Whenever I’m playing,

139
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:01,708
I feel more confident

140
00:06:01,791 --> 00:06:03,458
and always know
what to say.

141
00:06:03,541 --> 00:06:04,958
But real life’s
a different story.

142
00:06:05,041 --> 00:06:07,041
If I was invisible,
would anyone notice

143
00:06:07,125 --> 00:06:08,458
I was missing?

144
00:06:08,541 --> 00:06:10,875
Sometimes it’s like
I don’t even exist.

145
00:06:10,958 --> 00:06:12,875
Then you have
someone like Farin.

146
00:06:12,958 --> 00:06:15,125
Exceptional in the game
and real life.

147
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:16,125
Check her out.

148
00:06:16,208 --> 00:06:17,541
Talk about
my dream girl!

149
00:06:17,625 --> 00:06:18,708
I think she’s new.

150
00:06:18,791 --> 00:06:19,875
A transfer student?

151
00:06:19,958 --> 00:06:21,166
[SUIGIN]
At least I got it over with

152
00:06:21,250 --> 00:06:23,541
and she knows
how lame I really am.

153
00:06:23,625 --> 00:06:24,916
Wonder what she’s
gonna say next.

154
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,708
-[WAITRESS] Excuse me, sir.
-[grunts]

155
00:06:26,791 --> 00:06:27,833
You’ve been
here an hour

156
00:06:27,916 --> 00:06:29,208
and only ordered water.

157
00:06:29,291 --> 00:06:30,625
Perhaps it’s time
you committed to

158
00:06:30,708 --> 00:06:31,833
ordering food.

159
00:06:31,916 --> 00:06:33,375
You do realize
we have other students

160
00:06:33,458 --> 00:06:35,166
waiting to be seated?

161
00:06:35,250 --> 00:06:36,583
Sometime
today’d be nice.

162
00:06:36,666 --> 00:06:38,333
More like
anytime this week.

163
00:06:38,416 --> 00:06:39,500
I’m starving.

164
00:06:39,583 --> 00:06:40,458
Over there.

165
00:06:40,541 --> 00:06:41,625
Isn’t that
the poor kid

166
00:06:41,708 --> 00:06:43,166
hogging that table
and not ordering?

167
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:45,958
[yelps]
Give me that menu!

168
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:47,916
[FARIN] May I get one
to look at, as well?

169
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,208
Sure, here you go.

170
00:06:49,291 --> 00:06:50,875
Uh, so Farin,

171
00:06:50,958 --> 00:06:52,583
what are you
in the mood to eat?

172
00:06:52,666 --> 00:06:54,208
It all looks
so delicious.

173
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:56,958
One avocado salad,
minestrone soup,

174
00:06:57,041 --> 00:06:59,166
the escargot,
fried chicken wings,

175
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:01,916
a Teriyaki steak,
squid tempura.

176
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:02,916
[SUIGIN]
She’s bite size.

177
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:03,833
How can
she scarf down

178
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:05,208
more food
than she weighs?

179
00:07:05,291 --> 00:07:07,208
Her metabolism must be
a miracle of science.

180
00:07:07,291 --> 00:07:09,041
No! More importantly,
who's gonna

181
00:07:09,125 --> 00:07:10,958
pay for this
mountain of food?

182
00:07:11,041 --> 00:07:12,791
The only money
in my wallet right now

183
00:07:12,875 --> 00:07:15,583
is too embarrassing
to mention.

184
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:17,375
You’re not
just poor, Suigin.

185
00:07:17,458 --> 00:07:19,375
You are the King
of being poor!

186
00:07:19,458 --> 00:07:20,916
All that money
in the game,

187
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,416
and it’s absolutely
useless in real life.

188
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,500
If only I could pay
for things with it!

189
00:07:25,583 --> 00:07:26,916
[FARIN]
Chilled ham pizza.

190
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,666
Alfredo pasta. Oh!

191
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:30,416
-[FARIN] And the tiramisu!
-Should we dine and dash?

192
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:32,875
No! I won’t start a life of
crime over lunch!

193
00:07:32,958 --> 00:07:34,958
[FARIN]
Ice cream and cheesecake.

194
00:07:35,041 --> 00:07:36,791
[beeping]

195
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:39,041
♪

196
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:40,375
[WAITRESS]
Okay, sir.

197
00:07:40,458 --> 00:07:41,958
If you would choose
your form of payment.

198
00:07:42,041 --> 00:07:43,250
Uh...

199
00:07:43,333 --> 00:07:44,250
[WAITRESS]
Before patrons get their food,

200
00:07:44,333 --> 00:07:45,541
they must pay in advance.

201
00:07:45,625 --> 00:07:47,000
No problem at all!

202
00:07:47,083 --> 00:07:48,375
[SUIGIN]
“No problem?”

203
00:07:48,458 --> 00:07:51,333
I just agreed to eat here
and I have no cash!

204
00:07:51,416 --> 00:07:52,375
Sorry!

205
00:07:52,458 --> 00:07:53,333
If that’s not
enough food,

206
00:07:53,416 --> 00:07:54,333
we can order more.

207
00:07:54,416 --> 00:07:56,000
-You want to?
-More food?

208
00:07:56,083 --> 00:07:57,291
Oh, I couldn’t!

209
00:07:57,375 --> 00:07:59,250
You see, I’m actually
on a strict diet!

210
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:01,000
[SUIGIN]
My wallet’s the one starving!

211
00:08:01,083 --> 00:08:03,125
I’m about to go
bankrupt for one meal.

212
00:08:03,208 --> 00:08:04,375
[GUY 1]
What’s a pool boy

213
00:08:04,458 --> 00:08:06,250
doing at a posh
restaurant like this?

214
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:07,708
You weren’t
expecting this young lady

215
00:08:07,791 --> 00:08:10,041
to foot the bill
were you, Suigin?

216
00:08:10,125 --> 00:08:11,583
Actually,
weren’t you going after Rei

217
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:12,875
the other day?

218
00:08:12,958 --> 00:08:14,791
Looks like something
changed your mind.

219
00:08:14,875 --> 00:08:16,500
Maybe her dad dying?

220
00:08:16,583 --> 00:08:18,000
Do I have to
spell it out?

221
00:08:18,083 --> 00:08:20,041
Trash doesn’t belong here.

222
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:21,750
So why don’t you
give us your table?

223
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,375
-[FARIN] Apologize.
-What?

224
00:08:23,458 --> 00:08:25,750
I won’t allow you to talk
to my leader that way.

225
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:27,250
[GUY 1]
Your leader?

226
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:30,041
Suigin’s in charge of
our party in Grave Buster!

227
00:08:30,125 --> 00:08:31,916
And worth over
a hundred million.

228
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,875
So, he’s rich?

229
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:35,125
[chuckles nervously]

230
00:08:35,208 --> 00:08:37,375
Uh, only when
I’m in the game.

231
00:08:37,458 --> 00:08:39,166
[laughs hysterically]

232
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:41,208
-[ALL laugh]
-Now, that's hilarious!

233
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:43,291
The little girl’s
a comedic genius!

234
00:08:43,375 --> 00:08:44,708
[GUY 1] Hate to
break it to you, honey,

235
00:08:44,791 --> 00:08:46,250
but this guy’s a liar.

236
00:08:47,208 --> 00:08:48,875
Look, whatever he
told you is crap.

237
00:08:48,958 --> 00:08:50,541
-He wants to swindle you.
-It’s not a lie!

238
00:08:50,625 --> 00:08:53,666
Oh, yeah?
Prove it.

239
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:55,208
Go right ahead
and pay your bill

240
00:08:55,291 --> 00:08:56,791
using all those
Shinryou coins

241
00:08:56,875 --> 00:08:58,083
you claim you have.

242
00:08:58,166 --> 00:08:59,958
Huh? You can use Shinryou coins

243
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:01,583
in the game
and real life?

244
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:02,666
Sure.

245
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:03,833
We accept
that currency

246
00:09:03,916 --> 00:09:05,416
as well as
several other forms

247
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,166
of e-money
at this establishment.

248
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:08,750
But, how?

249
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:11,500
[WAITRESS] I’ll just need to
scan your Seabay, sir.

250
00:09:11,583 --> 00:09:13,958
[GUY 1] Yeah, yeah.
Hurry up and get it over with.

251
00:09:14,041 --> 00:09:15,833
I wanna prove this
bastard’s a con artist

252
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:17,166
once and for all.

253
00:09:18,166 --> 00:09:21,125
♪

254
00:09:21,208 --> 00:09:22,250
[beeping]

255
00:09:23,750 --> 00:09:25,291
[chuckles]

256
00:09:36,458 --> 00:09:39,000
Thank you, sir,
for your payment.

257
00:09:39,083 --> 00:09:40,333
It went through?

258
00:09:40,416 --> 00:09:42,291
You sure your scanner
isn’t broken?

259
